OL,6,F"We will urgently raise this with the
OL,7,Fauthorities in Hong Kong and Beijing
OL,8,Fto demand an explanation."
OL,10,FIn addition to being a member of Ipac,
OL,11,FMs Hobhouse has previously spoken out
OL,12,Fagainst the Chinese government's abuse
OL,13,Fof human rights in Tibet and crackdown
OL,14,Fon freedom of speech in Hong Kong.
OL,16,FChina has previously banned several
OL,17,FBritish MPs from entering the country,
OL,18,Fincluding Ipac members Sir Iain Duncan
OL,19,FSmith and Nusrat Ghani, and former
OL,20,Fsecurity minister Tom Tugendhat.
